      "message": "Just to nitpick (and this applies to the existing SkEnumerate)...\n\nTechnically to be an input_iterator it is also necessary to implement\n\nFoo* operator-\u003e();\n\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/27582845/how-to-implement-operator-for-an-iterator-that-constructs-its-values-on-demand\n\nFor example\n\nclass Iterator {\npublic:\nusing value_type \u003d ...;\nstruct PointerProxy {\n  value_type value;\n  value_type operator*()\u0026\u0026 { return value; }\n  value_type* operator-\u003e() { return \u0026value; }\n};\nPointerProxy operator-\u003e() { return {**this}; } // short for \u0027return {this-\u003eoperator*()};\u0027\n};",
